<section id="fs-id1167836540486" class="key-concepts">
<title>Key Concepts</title>
<list id="fs-id1167836341093" list-type="bulleted" bullet-style="bullet"><item><emphasis effect="bold">Change-of-Base Formula</emphasis><newline/><newline/>
<para id="eip-idm419567776">For any logarithmic base <m:math><m:mi>b</m:mi><m:mo>,</m:mo></m:math> where <m:math><m:mi>b</m:mi><m:mo>&gt;</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mi>b</m:mi><m:mo>≠</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:math>, and <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mo>&gt;</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para><equation id="eip-idm640117760"><m:math>
  <m:mtable columnalign="left">
   <m:mtr>
    <m:mtd>
     <m:msub>
      <m:mi>log</m:mi>
      <m:mi>b</m:mi>
     </m:msub>
     <m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac>
      <m:mrow>
       <m:mi>log</m:mi><m:mi>M</m:mi></m:mrow>
      <m:mrow>
       <m:mi>log</m:mi><m:mi>b</m:mi></m:mrow>
     </m:mfrac>
     <m:mtext>     or     </m:mtext><m:msub>
      <m:mi>log</m:mi>
      <m:mi>b</m:mi>
     </m:msub>
     <m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac>
      <m:mrow>
       <m:mi>ln</m:mi><m:mi>M</m:mi></m:mrow>
      <m:mrow>
       <m:mi>ln</m:mi><m:mi>b</m:mi></m:mrow>
     </m:mfrac>
     
    </m:mtd>
   </m:mtr>
   <m:mtr>
    <m:mtd>
     <m:mrow/>
    </m:mtd>
   </m:mtr>
   <m:mtr>
    <m:mtd>
     <m:mtext>   new base 10                    new base e</m:mtext>
    </m:mtd>
   </m:mtr>
  </m:mtable>  
</m:math>
</equation></item></list></section>
<section id="fs-id1167829579253" class="section-exercises">
<section id="fs-id1167829579256" class="practice-perfect">
<title>Practice Makes Perfect</title>
<para id="fs-id1167829752238"><emphasis effect="bold">Use the Change-of-Base Formula</emphasis></para>
<para id="fs-id1167829752244">In the following exercises, use the Change-of-Base Formula, rounding to three decimal places, to approximate each logarithm.</para>
